cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Implementation Performance Evaluation Across Multiple Configurations and
  Nodes
abstract: This dataset documents an experiment evaluating the performance of several
  QUIC implementations under varying network conditions. The methodology involved
  automated setup of nodes, disabling time synchronization, installing dependencies,
  compiling multiple QUIC libraries (lsquic, picoquic, quic-go, quiche, tquic, aioquic),
  and executing client-server transfer tests with bandwidth limiting.  Evaluation
  scripts aggregated results from repeated runs to generate reports and plots of goodput
  versus bandwidth limit for each implementation across different file sizes and configurations.
  Per-run logs and checksums are included alongside evaluation outputs.
